DB- server specific for data storage.
Types of DB- 
Relational / Structured :
1.MySql
2.postgres
Non-relational / Unstructured:
1.Mongodb
2.pinecone

Relational Vs Non-relational
1.Structured (data is stored as tables) | Unstructured (Data is stored as files, json, key value pairs)
2.schema (constraints) | No/loose schema
3.Read operation is fast bcz of indexing | Write operation is fast 
4.Scale(add) them horizontally | Scaled in both vertically and horizontally
 Horizontal - Increasing the no. of servers or clusters. (this is better since many servers are working)
 Vertical- Increasing the space of existing server
 